-- Ifo Sees Greek Euro Exit Costing Germany $99 Billion, Bild Says
-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 2012-07-24T19:40:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-24/ifo-sees-greek-euro-exit-costing-germany-99-billion-bild-says.html
A Greek insolvency and euro exit
would cost Germany as much as 82 billion euros ($99 billion),
 Bild  reported, citing the Ifo research institute.  Greece  remaining in the euro after insolvency would cost
German taxpayers as much as 89 billion euros, the newspaper
said, citing the Munich-based research institute as saying in an
e-mailed preview of a story to be published tomorrow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
